Third-party components and data

AMRFinderPlus (NCBI) — public domain, U.S. Government work.
    https://github.com/ncbi/amr

BV-BRC (Bacterial and Viral Bioinformatics Resource Center) — the laboratory
susceptibility data in data/cohort/ and data/real/ is derived from BV-BRC's
public release. See https://www.bv-brc.org for their terms and citation
guidance.

This MIT licence covers the code in this repository. It does not extend to
the third-party data above, which remains under its own terms.

---

Not a medical device

This software is a research prototype. It is not approved, cleared, or
validated for clinical use, and it must not be used to make treatment
decisions. Every prediction requires confirmation by standard laboratory
susceptibility testing and review by a qualified professional.
